cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with detecting near-duplicate recipes. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The proposed method aims to improve the retrieval of similar recipes, which falls under the scope of information retrieval. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a Skip-Gram model with negative sampling and fastText to extract candidate pairs of near-duplicate recipes, which are machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method uses word embedding and character 3-gram embedding, which are AI techniques. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning): Although the paper does not explicitly mention deep learning, the use of word embedding and character 3-gram embedding can be considered as deep learning techniques.
